# Spotify Clone Web Application

Build a pixel-perfect Spotify clone using vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript that supports song search and playback via the Deezer API (free, no auth required, provides 30-second previews).

## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup

#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Desktop/f1_strategy_project/spotify-clone/index.html)
Single-page HTML file with Spotify's layout structure:
- Sidebar (navigation, playlist list)
- Main content area (home view, search results)
- Bottom player bar (album art, controls, progress, volume)
- Uses Google Fonts (Circular/Inter), Font Awesome icons

---

### Styling

#### [NEW] [style.css](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Desktop/f1_strategy_project/spotify-clone/style.css)
Complete CSS matching Spotify's dark theme:
- Colors: `#121212` background, `#1DB954` green accent, `#181818` cards, `#b3b3b3` muted text
- Responsive grid layout (sidebar + main + player bar)
- Card components for albums/playlists
- Search bar styling
- Player bar with progress slider
- Hover effects, smooth transitions, glassmorphism on cards
- Custom scrollbar styling
- Animations for loading states

---

### Application Logic

#### [NEW] [app.js](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Desktop/f1_strategy_project/spotify-clone/app.js)
Core application JavaScript:
- **Deezer API Integration**: Search songs, fetch charts/trending, get artist info via `https://corsproxy.io/?https://api.deezer.com/`
- **Search**: Real-time search with debounce, display track results with album art
- **Music Player**: HTML5 Audio API playback, play/pause, next/previous, progress bar seek, volume control
- **Queue Management**: Play queue, skip forward/back
- **Home Page**: Display trending/chart tracks on load
- **UI State**: View switching (home/search), active track highlighting
- **Playlist Feature**: Create and manage local playlists (localStorage)

---

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
1. Open `spotify-clone/index.html` in a browser via a local server
2. Verify the dark theme UI matches Spotify's look
3. Test search: type an artist/song name → results appear with album art
4. Test playback: click a song → audio plays, player bar updates with track info
5. Test controls: play/pause, next/prev, seek via progress bar, volume slider
6. Test responsiveness: resize window → layout adapts
